The web isn't luxury. It's a lifeline that billions of people around the world are relying on during the #Covid19 crisis. But billions more are without access, cut off from this critical resource at a time when they need it most. Now's the time to fix that.

We're missing targets on global connectivity. It’s time to recognise that internet access is a public good and a basic right — and work to bring it to everyone. https://webfoundation.org/2020/04/covid-missed-targets/

Internet access is: A basic right A vital public good A lifeline Internet access is not: A luxury If ever there was a time to redouble efforts to bring the benefits of the internet to more people, it's now.

In the current #Covid19 crisis, deep digital inequalities have become even more glaring. Without urgent action, we will not only miss global targets to connect everyone — we will miss them by decades. @carlosiglesias explains our analysis

46% of the world: Doesn’t have health advice at their fingertips Can’t check in with friends and family by video call Can't work or learn from home At a time when internet access is critical, we're missing targets to connect everyone. https://webfoundation.org/2020/04/covid-missed-targets/
Can you imagine living through the #Covid19 crisis without access to the web? That's the reality faced by billions of people across the globe. We must take urgent action to connect the unconnected.
